# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml

# Test / coverage / scratch
coverage/
.nyc_output/
/tmp-*/

# Kotlin / Gradle build artifacts (if the template dir is built locally)
**/build/
**/.gradle/
**/.kotlin/
**/local.properties

# iOS build artifacts (Pods & generated Xcode project are not committed)
**/Pods/
**/*.xcworkspace
**/DerivedData/
iosApp/*.xcodeproj

# NOTE: the template ships *placeholder* google-services.json / GoogleService-Info.plist
# on purpose (the stamped build needs them to stay green), so they are intentionally
# NOT ignored here. Downstream generated projects should ignore their real ones.

# Internal working docs — not for the public repo
docs/DESIGN.md
docs/CONTRACT.md
docs/GROWTH-STRATEGY.md
docs/research/
docs/SESSION-STATE.md
docs/HARNESS-ROADMAP.md

# Inspector — generated headless-render output (the committed fixtures are
# inspector/harness/sample-*.json, not the per-run out/ dir).
inspector/harness/out/

# Canary version-set run outputs (qa-artifacts/canary/*.json) — generated by the
# canary lane, hashed into receipts but NEVER committed (template/CLAUDE.md,
# qa/lib/inputs-hash.mjs EXCLUDED_PREFIXES). Matches the template's own .gitignore.
qa-artifacts/
